<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxyc577d6fa0c114bb68493b38451e386b9-2">Accommodation</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Access to TV<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="no">Internet access<span class="hidden"> (no)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Public telephone<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Family accommodation <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Mobile phones permitted<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Private rooms only<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Single sex accommodation only<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContent086d216e9ad04713a33dd7a3f81e3c8d">
</div>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxyc577d6fa0c114bb68493b38451e386b9-4">Counselling and Support</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Bereavement support<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Translation services<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContent57f3121b6d4c43ae9211072c550f2fbf">
</div>
<p>The Patient Advice and Liaison Service provides an independent service for patients, carers and their families, providing information and resolving difficulties. To contact PALS Tel: 0800 019 3282; Email: pals.gloucestershirehospitals@glos.nhs.uk<br/>Text : 07827 281266<br/><br/>The Bereavement Office provides support and advice to close relatives or next of kin when someone dies in hospital.<br/>Contact 08454 224753. If you hear the answer phone please leave a message and this will be returned as soon as possible.<br/><br/></p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxyc577d6fa0c114bb68493b38451e386b9-5">Faith services</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Prayer area<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">On-site chapel<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContentdb3fce6ae1d94c858bbd4d757b798b76">
</div>
<p>The Trust has a Spiritual Care Team which exists to help and support patients’ own spiritual beliefs and religious practice during a stay in hospital.<br/>The hospital chaplain is available 24 hours a day and nursing staff can contact the chaplain on behalf of a patient. Members of the spiritual care team are also pleased to offer a confidential listening service, and to talk or pray with patients. They will also arrange spiritual and religious care appropriate to an individual patient’s needs.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="col clear facility">
<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxyc577d6fa0c114bb68493b38451e386b9-6">Food and amenities on-site</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="yes">Cafe<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">Patient library <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Pharmacy<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
<li class="yes">Shop<span class="hidden"> (yes)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContent9a1ff50f295746abbc26e2c53824702b">
</div>
<p>Induction loops and Signing Service are available in our hospitals. The Trust endeavours to provide the same standard of care regardles of a patient's communication difficulties or disability.</p>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last">
